## Data Schema Design

### Layer 1: Merchant Request Schema (Inbound)

What merchants send to us.

#### Base Event Fields

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `event_id` | string (UUID) | Yes | Unique identifier for this event (used for idempotency) |
| `event_type` | enum | Yes | One of: `ORDER_RECEIVED`, `ORDER_SHIPPED`, `ORDER_DELIVERED`, `ORDER_CANCELLED`, `ORDER_REFUNDED`, `ITEM_RETURNED`, `FULFILLMENT_DELAYED` |
| `event_timestamp` | string (ISO 8601) | Yes | When the event occurred |
| `merchant_order_number` | string (1-256 chars) | Yes | Merchant's order identifier (links to original checkout) |
| `payload` | object | Yes | Event-specific data (see below) |

#### Event Payloads

**ORDER_RECEIVED**

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `estimated_ship_date` | string (ISO 8601) | No | When merchant expects to ship |
| `estimated_delivery` | string (ISO 8601) | No | Projected delivery date |
| `processing_status` | enum | No | `CONFIRMED`, `PREPARING`, `READY_TO_SHIP` |
| `items_confirmed` | array | No | Items with `sku`, `quantity`, `in_stock` |
| `order_notes` | string | No | Optional message from merchant |

**ORDER_SHIPPED**

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `carrier` | string | Yes | Shipping carrier name |
| `tracking_number` | string | Yes | Carrier tracking number |
| `tracking_url` | string (URL) | No | Direct link to tracking page |
| `shipped_items` | array | Yes | Items with `sku`, `quantity` |
| `estimated_delivery` | string (ISO 8601) | No | Expected delivery date |

**ORDER_DELIVERED**

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `delivered_at` | string (ISO 8601) | Yes | Delivery timestamp |
| `delivery_location` | enum | No | `FRONT_DOOR`, `MAILBOX`, `LOCKER`, `SIGNED`, `OTHER` |
| `signature_name` | string | No | Name of person who signed |

**ORDER_CANCELLED**

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `cancelled_by` | enum | Yes | `MERCHANT` or `CUSTOMER` |
| `reason` | string | No | Cancellation reason |
| `cancelled_items` | array | No | Items with `sku`, `quantity` (if omitted, entire order cancelled) |

**ORDER_REFUNDED**

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `refund_type` | enum | Yes | `FULL` or `PARTIAL` |
| `refund_amount.value` | string | Yes | Refund amount |
| `refund_amount.currency_code` | string (3 chars) | Yes | ISO 4217 currency code |
| `refunded_items` | array | No | Items with `sku`, `quantity` |
| `reason` | string | No | Refund reason |

**ITEM_RETURNED**

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `return_status` | enum | Yes | `INITIATED`, `IN_TRANSIT`, `RECEIVED`, `PROCESSED` |
| `returned_items` | array | Yes | Items with `sku`, `quantity` |
| `return_tracking_number` | string | No | Return shipment tracking |
| `refund_issued` | boolean | Yes | Whether refund has been issued |

**FULFILLMENT_DELAYED**

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `original_estimated_delivery` | string (ISO 8601) | Yes | Previous delivery estimate |
| `new_estimated_delivery` | string (ISO 8601) | Yes | Updated delivery estimate |
| `reason` | string | No | Reason for delay |

### Layer 2: LLM Partner Notification Schema (Outbound)

What we send to LLM partners:

```typescript
const LLMPartnerNotificationSchema = z.object({
  // Routing info for the LLM partner
  notification_id: z.string().uuid(),
  notification_type: z.literal("ORDER_UPDATE"),
  timestamp: z.string().datetime(),

  // Order context - enables LLM to correlate with original purchase
  order_context: z.object({
    merchant_order_number: z.string(),
    merchant_name: z.string(),
    merchant_id: z.string(),
    original_purchase_timestamp: z.string().datetime().optional(),
  }),

  // Human-readable summary for LLM consumption
  update_summary: z.object({
    event_type: z.string(),
    headline: z.string(),        // e.g., "Your order has shipped!"
    details: z.string(),         // e.g., "Tracking: 1Z999..."
    action_url: z.string().url().optional(),
    next_expected_event: z.string().optional(),
  }),

  // Structured data for programmatic use
  structured_data: z.object({
    event_type: z.string(),
    // Event-specific fields flattened
    // Carrier, tracking, amounts, etc.
  }).passthrough(),
});
```

### Transformation Logic

```typescript
function transformToPartnerSchema(
  webhookEvent: MerchantWebhookEvent,
  merchantContext: MerchantContext
): LLMPartnerNotification {
  return {
    notification_id: crypto.randomUUID(),
    notification_type: "ORDER_UPDATE",
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),

    order_context: {
      merchant_order_number: webhookEvent.merchant_order_number,
      merchant_name: merchantContext.merchantName,
      merchant_id: merchantContext.merchantId,
    },

    update_summary: generateHumanReadableSummary(webhookEvent),

    structured_data: {
      event_type: webhookEvent.event_type,
      ...webhookEvent.payload,
    },
  };
}

function generateHumanReadableSummary(event: MerchantWebhookEvent): UpdateSummary {
  switch (event.event_type) {
    case "ORDER_RECEIVED":
      return {
        event_type: "ORDER_RECEIVED",
        headline: "Your order has been received!",
        details: event.payload.estimated_ship_date
          ? `Expected to ship by ${event.payload.estimated_ship_date}`
          : "The merchant is processing your order.",
        next_expected_event: "ORDER_SHIPPED",
      };
    case "ORDER_SHIPPED":
      return {
        event_type: "ORDER_SHIPPED",
        headline: "Your order has shipped!",
        details: `Carrier: ${event.payload.carrier}. Tracking: ${event.payload.tracking_number}`,
        action_url: event.payload.tracking_url,
        next_expected_event: "ORDER_DELIVERED",
      };
    // ... other cases
  }
}
```

